  "text": "CT perfusion is a new method to analyze dynamic changes in liver tumors. Studies [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] showed that hepatic blood flow, hepatic arterial perfusion, and hepatic portal perfusion were significantly increased in the tumor edges of HCC patients. CT perfusion of tumors may be helpful in revealing histopathological features, as well as indirectly reflecting angiogenic changes.",
